<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY SPORTS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CAL LUTHERAN FALLS TO WESTMONT, 90-83 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five players scored in double figures for Westmont College in a 90-83 victory 
over Cal Lutheran in a NAIA District 3 basketball game Monday night at Cal 
Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
Chad Kammerer scored 22 points and Chris Hahs scored 16 points and grabbed a 
game-high 14 rebounds for Westmont (3-1, 1-0 in district play), which had a 
52-35 edge in rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff de Laveaga scored a game-high 31 points for Cal Lutheran (1-3, 0-2), which 
stayed close by making 10 of 19 three-point shots. 
</P>
<P>
Joe Cohen (14 points), Carl Champion (14) and Simon O'Donnell (12) scored in 
double figures for Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 65, Dos Pueblos 46 -- Jason Harper scored a game-high 16 points to 
lead Glendale (2-2) in a consolation-bracket game of the Simi Valley 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Wright added 14 points for Glendale, which finished in 11th place. 
</P>
<P>
Alemany 57, Oxnard 56 -- Richard Dice scored a game-high 20 points to lead 
Alemany (2-2) in a consolation-bracket game of the Simi Valley tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Antonio Williams led Oxnard (1-3) with 19 points. Will Burr scored 17 points 
for Alemany, which finished in 13th place. 
</P>
<P>
Canoga Park 92, Sylmar 57 -- Chris Ofstad, a 6-foot-6 senior, scored 16 points 
and added nine rebounds for Canoga Park in a consolation-bracket game of the 
Simi Valley tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Senior guard Lindsey Dunbar scored a game-high 17 points for Canoga Park (2-3), 
which finished 15th. 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 79, Hueneme 77 -- Hueneme, which trailed by seven points with 1 minute 
17 seconds left, came up short when Tony Smith's driving, contested lay-in came 
up short in a semifinal game of the Bishop Amat tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Dwine Knott scored 20 points, Smith had 19, and Wendell Nunnery added 17 for 
Hueneme (1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 118, Glendale Academy 38 -- Thirteen players scored for Harvard in a 
first-round game of the Faith Baptist tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Markus Puhvel led Harvard (1-1) with 18 points and teammate Iheanyi Uwaezuoke, 
who made seven of 10 shots from the field, scored 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
