<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: INTERNATIONAL SPORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Treasury Department has agreed to allow ABC have exclusive rights to 
televise the 1991 Pan American Games from Cuba to the United States. 
</P>
<P>
The games are scheduled for August. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement settles a six-month-old lawsuit in which a federal judge in New 
York upheld the Treasury Department's right to block the network from paying 
Cuba a rights fee for the games. Details were not disclosed. 
</P>
