<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jeffrey A. Perlman and Kathie Bozanich 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SLOW GOING: Few will be surprised by the commuting habits (above) revealed in 
the newest Orange County Annual Survey: Most people drive to work alone, half 
of them on freeways, in virtually identical proportions as in 1982. . . . How 
does this reconcile with the survey's finding of increased concern for the 
environment (A1)? When it comes to commuting, "people don't perceive that they 
have significant alternatives at this point," says pollster Mark Baldassare. 
"It's just not as easy as recycling." 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
HOW WE GET TO WORK 
</P>
<P>
1990 figures 
</P>
<P>
Drive alone: 83% 
</P>
<P>
Over 20 minutes: 39% 
</P>
<P>
Use freeways: 50% 
</P>
<P>
Work outside Orange County: 17% 
</P>
<P>
Source: Orange County Annual Surveys, UCI Jeffrey A. Perlman and Kathie 
Bozanich 
</P>
</TEXT>
