<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-HOSTAGE PRAISES CAPTORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American missionary Stephen Schaeffer said Monday that he and New Zealand 
missionary John Marsh were treated well during their 12 days as hostages of 
Papuan rebels fighting for independence of Indonesian-ruled Irian Jaya. 
Schaeffer said they had not felt threatened by their captors and had kept up 
their spirits by praying daily in the guerrillas' jungle hide-out until their 
release last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
