ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
CANDLELIGHT VIGIL PLANNED FOR FRIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In observance of International Human Rights Day, the Orange County chapter of 
Amnesty International USA will sponsor a candlelight vigil Friday night in the 
downtown area. 
</P>
<P>
The vigil, which is aimed at calling attention to human rights abuses 
throughout the world, will take place at Chapman Avenue and Glassell Street 
from 7 to 9. Participants are asked to bring candles, flashlights and signs or 
banners. 
</P>
<P>
International Human Rights Day is Monday. For information, call (714) 998-0724. 
</P>
</TEXT>
