<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALL-ACADEMIC TEAM NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rams and GTE will honor its first all-Orange County Academic High School 
Football team Sunday before the Rams' game with the New Orleans Saints at 
Anaheim Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
The minimum criteria was achieving a grade-point average of at least 3.0 and 
earning at least second-team all-league honors. 
</P>
<P>
Offense 
</P>
<P>
Line: Jeff Dorsz (Troy), Steve Miller (Orange), Karl Shroller (Fountain 
Valley), Paul Richard (Valencia) and Ben Seguia (Brea-Olinda); QB: Rob Johnson 
(El Toro). Back: Visko Ancich (Tustin) and Mike Sullivan (Sunny Hills); TE: 
Reid Pullen (Esperanza); Rec: David Shearer (Santa Margarita) and Tyler Cashman 
(Los Alamitos); K: Doug Roberson (Mission Viejo). 
</P>
<P>
Defense 
</P>
<P>
Line: Jeremy Hogue (El Toro), Damon Becknel (Villa Park), Brian Pearsall (Villa 
Park) and Ismael Lopez (Anaheim); LB: David Phillips (Costa Mesa), Mike Silvey 
(Mater Dei) and Greg Livermore (La Quinta); Back: Bill Denny (Mission Viejo), 
Mike Ryan (Brea-Olinda), Eric Davis (Laguna Hills) and Eric Moore (Rancho 
Alamitos); P: Trevor Yankoff (Santa Margarita). 
</P>
</TEXT>
