Visa Imposes Membership Moratorium: Visa U.S.A. said the six-month moratorium 
on allowing new applicants from non-banking companies to issue its credit cards 
was a "prudent measure" while it reviews Visa membership eligibility in 
general. Institutions not eligible to join Visa directly would not be allowed 
to join indirectly by merging or acquiring a member company without the 
approval of Visa's board, the company said. 
