MORNING REPORT: DANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABT Dancers' New Contract: American Ballet Theatre dancers are expected in the 
rehearsal studio today following an agreement reached midnight Friday after an 
intense 10-hour negotiating session. Dancers won a $2 increase per day, but 
will double up in hotel rooms for two foreign tours. For domestic tours -- such 
as the Orange County Performing Arts Center in March -- dancers will get 
individual rooms. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
