<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAROLD HILDEBRAND; FORMER PUBLICIST, REVIEWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harold Hildebrand, former drama reviewer and entertainment publicist, has died 
at a Panorama City hospital. He was 67. 
</P>
<P>
A longtime Arleta resident, Hildebrand died Wednesday of cancer, said a close 
friend, Mike Mamakos. 
</P>
<P>
Born July 28, 1923, in Minneapolis, Hildebrand came to California as a infant, 
graduated from Hamilton High School in Los Angeles and served in the Navy 
during World War II. 
</P>
<P>
For more than 20 years, he was a reviewer and drama writer for the now-defunct 
Los Angeles Herald Examiner, later becoming a publicist in the entertainment 
field, representing performers and production companies. 
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his wife, Theresa; sons James Hildebrand of Los Angeles and 
David Hildebrand of Hollywood Hills; daughter Claudia Arenal of Canoga Park; 
brother Glen Hildebrand of San Francisco, and a granddaughter. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial Mass will be celebrated at noon Saturday at St. Genevieve's Catholic 
Church, 14061 Roscoe Blvd., Panorama City. 
</P>
<P>
Praiswater Funeral Home in Van Nuys is handling the arrangements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
