<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: HOUSE OF FABRICS REPORTS 5% GAIN IN PROFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
House of Fabrics, the Sherman Oaks-based home sewing and crafts chain, reported 
a 5% increase in earnings for the three months that ended Oct. 31, to $4.52 
million from $4.30 million over the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
Third-quarter sales rose 13% to $104.4 million, up from $92.5 million last 
year, the company reported. 
</P>
<P>
Gary L. Larkins, the company's president and chief executive officer, 
attributed the increase in part to the addition of larger stores with expanded 
inventories. 
</P>
<P>
Earnings for the nine months that ended Oct. 31 rose 33% to $7.36 million from 
$5.52 million in the same period a year earlier. Sales rose 10% to $278.1 
million from $253.3 million last year. 
</P>
<P>
The company operates 613 stores, and anticipates opening 10 additional stores 
and closing 18 before the end of the fiscal year, Larkins said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
