<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CAMARILLO COMMUNITY POSTS 30% RISE IN EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Camarillo Community Bank in Camarillo reported a 30% increase in earnings to 
$190,550 for the third quarter that ended Sept. 30, up from $145,821 a year 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Earnings for the first nine months of 1990 were up 6%, to $559,002, compared to 
$529,395 for the same period last year. The bank's total assets as of Sept. 30 
increased 16% to $62.9 million from $54.0 million over the same nine-month 
period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
