<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: FORTUNE PETROLEUM PROFIT IS $88,000 IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fortune Petroleum Corp., reaping the benefits of the surge in oil prices, said 
its third-quarter profit jumped to $88,000 from $4,000 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Fortune, a small energy concern based in Agoura Hills, said its revenue in the 
quarter that ended Sept. 30 climbed to $342,000 from $230,000. That's because 
the average price Fortune received for its oil in the latest quarter was $21.62 
a barrel, up from $13.80 a barrel in the second quarter. Oil prices rose 
sharply after Iraq's invasion of Kuwait Aug. 2. 
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, Fortune reported a $41,000 loss for the first nine months of this 
year on revenue of $793,000. A year earlier, it lost $36,000 on revenue of 
$734,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
