<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: ACCOUNTING FIRMS COMPLETE MERGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Sherman Oaks accounting firm Bridge &amp; Mischel has merged with Kirsch, 
Stein, Kohn &amp; Oster, an Encino accounting firm. 
</P>
<P>
The merger was completed Nov. 1. Named Kirsch, Kohn, Oster, Bridge &amp; 
Mischel, the new firm employs 50 people, becoming what company officials said 
is one of the largest accounting firms in the San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
