<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE COMMERCIAL VACANCY RATE FALLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The vacancy rate for commercial office space in Glendale fell 2 percentage 
points, to 10%, in the three months ended Sept. 30, according to a report by 
Grubb &amp; Ellis Commercial Real Estate Services. 
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the year, the vacancy rate in Glendale has fallen more 
than 4 points, the report stated. 
</P>
<P>
More office space was leased in the area this year than in the three previous 
years combined, it said. 
</P>
<P>
Total vacant square footage in the third quarter was 365,400, compared with 
371,250 between April and June. 
</P>
<P>
The report said occupied office space increased by 569,000 square feet in the 
third quarter, in large part because Carnation Co. moved into 300,000 square 
feet of office space in the company's recently completed building on Brand 
Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
An additional 100,000 square feet of the building was occupied by Walt Disney 
Imagineering. 
</P>
<P>
Other major leases signed in the third quarter included 43,000 square feet in 
the Koll Building and 35,000 square feet in the Glendale Corporate Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
