<P>
64 REPORTED DEAD IN FACTIONAL VIOLENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 64 people have been killed in an explosion of knife and gun battles 
for political supremacy in South African black townships, and military 
reinforcements were called in to help police restore order. The fighting 
erupted between residents loyal to Nelson Mandela's African National Congress 
and migrant workers sympathetic to the Zulu-based Inkatha Freedom Party. 
</P>
