<P>
GERMANY HUMS ON EAST'S NEEDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BONN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The western German economy continued to boom in the third quarter, sparked by 
increased domestic investments and high demand from the new eastern part of 
Germany, the Federal Statistics Office said today. 
</P>
<P>
Western Germany's gross national product soared 5.5% in the third quarter this 
year, compared to a year ago, it said. 
</P>
<P>
Increased investment activity within the country and high demand from eastern 
Germany, which became part of the Federal Republic on Oct. 3, boosted the GNP 
in the western part of the country, the report said. 
</P>
