<HEADLINE>
<P>
STOCKS IN TOKYO PLUMMET 4% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stock prices on the Tokyo Stock Exchange plummeted nearly 4% today as major 
players abandoned the field to margin selling and arbitrage. 
</P>
<P>
Trading remained light. 
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip Nikkei Average of 225 selected issues, which gained 271.36 points 
Monday, fell 863.38 points to close below the psychologically important 22,000 
mark at 21,862.61. 
</P>
<P>
But the figure many brokers pointed to was the low volume, which continued to 
dwindle as an estimated 240 million shares changed hands, down from 264 million 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
By comparison, a year ago, when the Nikkei was racing toward an all-time high, 
volume on Dec. 4 was 1.2 billion shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
