<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS OBTAIN OUTFIELDER IN 3-PLAYER DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROSEMONT, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Baltimore Orioles today traded outfielder Dave Gallagher to the California 
Angels for pitchers David Martinez and Mike Hook. 
</P>
<P>
Gallagher, 30, started the 1990 season with the Chicago White Sox and was 
claimed on waivers by Baltimore on Aug. 2. In 45 games for the Orioles, 
Gallagher hit .280. 
</P>
<P>
Gallagher is expected to back up newly acquired outfielder Junior Felix in 
center field. 
</P>
<P>
Martinez, 27, has a career minor-league record of 32-42. He has been placed on 
the Orioles' 40-man roster. 
</P>
<P>
Hook, 22, was a combined 6-4 for Quad City and Midland last season. Hook was 
assigned to Class AAA Rochester of the International League. 
</P>
