<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
GORMAN TO CAPTAIN U.S. DAVIS CUP TEAM FOR THE SIXTH TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tom Gorman, who led the U.S. Davis Cup team to victory over Australia last 
weekend, will stay on as captain in 1991, the U.S. Tennis Assn. announced 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Gorman, a player on the team that won the championship round in 1972, will be 
serving as captain for the sixth year. In addition to this year's triumph, he 
skippered the team that reached the semifinals in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
"Tom has brought America's Davis Cup program to heights all of us are extremely 
proud of," USTA President David Markin said in a statement. "He has shown 
sensitivity and leadership in what is a very public position and we are pleased 
to have him as our captain." 
</P>
</TEXT>
